Capital One Financial Corp. (COF) , the
lender that gets more than half its revenue from credit cards,
gave Chief Executive Officer Richard Fairbank about $17.5
million in compensation for 2012, according to the firm.  Fairbank received $10.9 million in stock and $4.38 million
in options, the McLean, Virginia-based company said in a filing
today. Fairbank, who doesnâ€™t draw a salary, also received a
$2.19 million cash bonus, the filing said.  Under guidelines from securities regulators, which
calculate pay differently, Fairbank earned $22.6 million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
